      "fontWeight": "normal",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\u2190 sin=0.50 for both!"
    },
    {
      "id": "e0351",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 7570,
      "y": 720,
      "width": 1600,
      "height": 40,
      "strokeColor": "#94A3B8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "frameId": "e0254",
      "roundness": null,
      "text": "Why BOTH sin AND cos?  sin(30\u00b0) = sin(150\u00b0) \u2014 ambiguous!  Only together do they give a unique point on the circle.",
      "fontSize": 17,
      "fontFamily": 2,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "fontWeight": "normal",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why BOTH sin AND cos?  sin(30\u00b0) = sin(150\u00b0) \u2014 ambiguous!  Only together do they give a unique point on the circle."
    },
    {
      "id": "e0352",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 7570,
      "y": 762,
      "width": 1600,
      "height": 40,
      "strokeColor": "#64748B",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "frameId": "e0254",
      "roundness": null,
      "text": "This same trick works for hours of the day, day of week, or any periodic variable.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 2,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "fontWeight": "normal",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "This same trick works for hours of the day, day of week, or any periodic variable."
    },
